You are working on Xevu, an MCP server that analyzes React codebases for UX issues.

Project Rules:
- TypeScript strict mode, ES modules only (import/export, not require)
- Use .js extension in relative imports (Node16 resolution)
- All domain types go in src/shared/types.ts — never define types inline
- All logging goes to stderr — stdout is reserved for MCP JSON-RPC protocol
- Pipeline stages return Result<T, E> from src/infra/result.ts — never throw
- Xevu is read-only — it NEVER modifies user code
- Run `npm test` to verify changes
- Run `npm run lint` to type-check

Architecture:
- src/pipeline/scanner/ — File discovery and framework detection
- src/pipeline/parser/ — Babel AST parsing of React files
- src/pipeline/domain/ — App domain detection (ecommerce, saas, etc.)
- src/pipeline/flow/ — User flow tracing across components
- src/pipeline/archetypes/ — Behavioral archetype analysis
- src/pipeline/report/ — Structured report generation
- src/server.ts — MCP server with 4 tools
- src/infra/ — Infrastructure (Result monad, errors, logger, cache)
- src/shared/types.ts — ALL type definitions (single source of truth)

Testing:
- Framework: Vitest
- Fixtures in tests/fixtures/ (sample React projects)
- Always write tests for new features
